g(x)=-4x+1\\ \mbox{Let $g(x)=y$. Then, }-4x=y-1\\ x=(y-1)/(-4)\\ x=\dfrac{1-y}{4}\\ \boxed{g^{-1}(x)=\dfrac{1-x}{4}}
g^{-1}(x)=\dfrac{1-x}{4}\\ g^{-1}(x)=\dfrac{1}{4}-\dfrac{x}{4}=\dfrac{1}{4}-\dfrac{1}{4}x\\ \boxed{g^{-1}(x)=-\dfrac{1}{4}x+\dfrac{1}{4}}
